"title": "2354: Jesus Christ, mission of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2354",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The work that Jesus Christ was sent to do, including both his healing and preaching ministry, but particularly his work of salvation. Jesus Christ sends Christians to continue his work by proclaiming his message of salvation.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ was called to his mission from the beginning of time</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:1\">ISA 49:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:2\">MIC 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:20\">1PE 1:20</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus' mission as Messiah was foretold</h2>\n<h3>His mission to help and heal the poor</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1-Isa61:3\">ISA 61:1–61:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:3-Isa11:5\">ISA 11:3–11:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:3-Isa32:4\">ISA 32:3–32:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:5-Isa35:6\">ISA 35:5–35:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:3\">ISA 42:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:7\">ISA 42:7</a></p>\n<h3>His mission to rule and establish the kingdom of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6-Isa9:7\">ISA 9:6–9:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:10\">GEN 49:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:11\">PSA 132:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:5-Jer23:6\">JER 23:5–23:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:44\">DAN 2:44</a></p>\n<h3>His mission to establish justice and peace</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:4-Isa11:5\">ISA 11:4–11:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:4\">ISA 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:4-Isa9:7\">ISA 9:4–9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:4\">ISA 42:4</a></p>\n<h3>His mission to suffer and die</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:3-Isa53:10\">ISA 53:3–53:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:6\">ISA 50:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:14\">ISA 52:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:26\">DAN 9:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31\">MRK 8:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:26-Luke24:27\">LUK 24:26–24:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:32-Acts8:35\">ACT 8:32–8:35</a></p>\n<h3>His mission was fulfilled in humility and poverty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:9\">ZEC 9:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:2-Isa42:3\">ISA 42:2–42:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:7\">ISA 49:7</a></p>\n<h3>His mission was for all nations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:6\">ISA 49:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:10\">ISA 11:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:1-Isa42:6\">ISA 42:1–42:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:4-Isa55:5\">ISA 55:4–55:5</a></p>\n<h2>Aspects of Jesus Christ's mission</h2>\n<h3>Preaching and teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:43\">LUK 4:43</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:38\">MRK 1:38</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:17\">MAT 4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:2\">MAT 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:21\">MRK 1:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:2\">JHN 8:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:37\">JHN 18:37</a></p>\n<h3>Sacrificial service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:27\">LUK 22:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:13-John13:16\">JHN 13:13–13:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:7\">PHP 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>Healing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:23\">MAT 4:23</a></strong> <em>A healing ministry was one of the signs of the expected Messiah.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:14\">MAT 14:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:34\">MRK 1:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:40\">LUK 4:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:15\">LUK 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:4-John9:7\">JHN 9:4–9:7</a></p>\n<h3>Judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:39\">JHN 9:39</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ does not come to condemn, but the response people make to him is the ultimate criterion of judgment. Those truly seeking God turn to faith in Jesus Christ; unbelievers, by their rejection of him, are confirmed in their unbelief.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:49\">LUK 12:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:17-John3:18\">JHN 3:17–3:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:22\">JHN 5:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:10-John8:11\">JHN 8:10–8:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:26\">JHN 8:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:47-John12:48\">JHN 12:47–12:48</a></p>\n<h2>Criteria for the direction of Jesus Christ's mission</h2>\n<h3>Obedience to his Father's will</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:38\">JHN 6:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39\">MAT 26:39</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:36\">MRK 14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:34\">JHN 4:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:31\">JHN 14:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:11\">JHN 18:11</a></p>\n<h3>The fulfilment of the Law and the Prophets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:17\">MAT 5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:35\">MAT 13:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:54\">MAT 26:54</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:18-Luke4:21\">LUK 4:18–4:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:31\">LUK 18:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:21\">ROM 3:21</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's saving death is the supreme aspect and focus of his mission</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ came to save and to give life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:10\">JHN 10:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:21\">MAT 1:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:10\">LUK 19:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:17\">JHN 3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:15\">1TI 1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:10\">2TI 1:10</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ came to suffer and to die</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:21\">MAT 16:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31\">MRK 8:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:22\">LUK 9:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:27\">JHN 12:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:24-Rom3:25\">ROM 3:24–3:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:20\">COL 1:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:10\">1JN 4:10</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ was aware of the personal cost of his mission</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:50\">LUK 12:50</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:38-Matt26:39\">MAT 26:38–26:39</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:34-Mark14:36\">MRK 14:34–14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a></p>\n<h2>The mission of Jesus Christ continues today</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's own work continues</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:24-Heb7:25\">HEB 7:24–7:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:34\">ROM 8:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:18\">ROM 15:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:10-2Cor4:11\">2CO 4:10–4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:20\">HEB 6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:12\">HEB 9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:14\">HEB 9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:21\">HEB 13:21</a></p>\n<h3>Christians are called to share in Jesus Christ's mission</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:21\">JHN 20:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:19–28:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:15\">MRK 16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:12\">JHN 14:12</a></p>",
